# Plan Catalog Update Playbook

When adding or changing any plan option, use the centralized catalog flow.

## Source of Truth

- Weekly and daily options must be defined in `lib/plans/catalog.ts`.
- Reuse helpers in `lib/plans/service.ts` instead of hardcoded IDs, prices, durations, or meal counts.
- Keep `planId` consistent with naming conventions (`weekly-{meals}x{weeks}`, `daily-{type}-{credits}`).

## Required Update Checklist

1. Update plan entries in `lib/plans/catalog.ts` (`active`, price, sort, tags as needed).
2. Verify UI screens read plans from service helpers (no local hardcoded arrays).
3. Verify request-creation APIs persist `planId` and derive pricing from service helpers.
4. Verify admin approve/export and email labels include the new option where applicable.
5. Verify balance logic supports the option via `planBalances` and compatibility fallbacks.
6. Run validation (`npm run lint` and `npx tsc --noEmit` if feasible) and test one daily + one weekly request path.

## Guardrails

- Do not duplicate plan definitions across components/APIs.
- Prefer extending catalog/service/balance utilities over adding one-off conditional branches.
- If legacy data needs backfill for new fields, add/update a script under `scripts/`.
